title: Cuddles [Yoongi x Reader]
body:
Requests are open!

Genre: Cute, fluff, romance

master list

~

It wasn’t necessarily easy for you to break down Yonngi’s walls. You knew going into this relationship that it was difficult mainly because he was so guarded, who wouldn’t be after the rough past he’s had? Your heart always felt heavy whenever he slightly opened up with how difficult things where. 

Showing him all the love and support was the best and what you believed one of the only options you could do. Besides being patience and waiting for him. Because of how often he worked, the both of you never really spent that much time together. It was always lovely text messages during the day, and maybe a half an hour to an hour at night over at the dorms. 

Your relationship with him was kept private for not only your sake, but for his sake. You knew the rules of his contract, and you knew what could happen to him if something like this were to come out. Which made it even more difficult to spend time with him, because you didn’t want the media to be all over something that was so sacred to you.  

“How was your day?” was the first question you asked considering both of you were on the couch cuddling. It was two or three in the morning on a weekend. You didn’t have any responsibilities the next day, so it was honestly alright for you to stay this long. 

“Like any other work day.” Yoongi responded softly, his head was bend to rest against the top of yours while the two of you cuddled together. Your hands were interlocked with his, which where smooth to the touch. For how often he plays the piano and works with his hands, you were always amazed by how smooth they were. 

Music was softly playing in the background while you two just sat in each others presents. You knew that you had to go home soon because his manager usually showed up to check up on them during the day. Of course the other members knew that both of you were a thing, it wasn’t a secret between them. It was always fun to watch them poke fun of Yoongi just to make him flustered. 

“When are you leaving for America?” You asked knowing that they were going back for their tour during the summer. You could feel his chest rising as you knew a sigh was about to leave. One of the more difficult parts about dating an idol other than keeping it secret was all of the concerts and tours they went on. It was almost as if out of the entire year, you only got to spend x amount of time with him. 

It was silent once again, Yoongi seemed to be deep in thought as the two of you were just resting away. Not only was it a difficult question to ask, but to Yoongi it was a difficult question to answer. He knew how hard it was to be away from you, and he knew that this relationship took a tool on you. But it didn’t seem to stop him, or make him afraid of pursuing you. When you came into his life just a couple of years ago, he was completely blown away by you. 

Not only where you there to help him through his rough times, but you were like a light to him. A burning fire one would often say. This relationship was something that he didn’t want to let go, and would fight for you no matter what happened. 

“End of April I think..” Yoongi whispers turning his head and kissing the top of yours. It was brief, but sweet. Something you wanted Yoongi to do more often. Although you never seemed to get your words out when you wanted them to. Instead of being a downer, you turned yourself around. Catching his eye while reaching out to grab his hands. 

Leaning forwards, you pressed your head against his, your faces just inches away from each other at this point. It was silent for a quick second before your words came out that made Yoongi’s heart flutter. “Then let’s make these next few months count Yoongi. I love you.” and instead of hearing him say anything back, he closed the space in by giving you a soft but loving kiss.
